 3-Day Rolling Average
From daily_sales, compute a 3-day rolling average of the amount (current day + 2 preceding days). Show: sale_date, amount, and rolling_avg_3d. Round to 2 decimal places.

💡 Hint
⚡ ROWS BETWEEN N PRECEDING

select sale_date, amount,
round(avg(amount) over (order by sale_date rows between 2 preceding and current row),2) as rolling_avg_3d
from daily_sales 

SQL
ROWS BETWEEN [start] AND [end]
Commonly used boundaries include:

UNBOUNDED PRECEDING: From the very first row of the partition.

UNBOUNDED FOLLOWING: To the very last row of the partition.

CURRENT ROW: The row currently being processed.

N PRECEDING: N rows before the current row.

N FOLLOWING: N rows after the current row.
